==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outcrop
<hw>Out"crop`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The coming out of a stratum to the surface of the
ground.</def> <au>Lyell.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>That part of inclined
strata which appears at the surface; basset.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outcrop</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Outcrop
<hw>Out*crop"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>To come out to the surface of the ground; -- said of
strata.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

